You decided to call the "Delta Force" directly. A team of highly trained experts storms into the room. **Confusion in Communication:** The "Delta Force" misinterprets your command and thinks Ameya is the victim. They end up surrounding Akshay and demand he explain himself. ''Technology Gone Wrong:'' One member of the Delta Force tries to disable Ameya's laptop but accidentally activates the //Rickroll Defense Mechanism//". Everyone is forced to listen to "Never Gonna Give You Up" on loop until Ameya's laptop battery dies. ''Ameya Escapes Anyway:'' While everyone is distracted, Ameya escapes through an air duct, leaving behind a sticky note that says: *"Football or nothing. Your move."* [[Keep the mission going]] [[withdraw the mission and accept the demands ->Listen to His Demands]](text-colour:green)[''Because of your decision''] -> jagan died listening to music because he was given a target to complete 900 minutes in 10 minutes -> Bhoopesh scheduled reviews for all the people at the same time 9:00 pm tommorrow. -> Revant is the happiest anyways (text-colour:red)[''UPTO TO YOU IF THE ENDING IS A HAPPY ENDING OR SAD''] (text-colour:red)[''You chose chaos over compliance''] ''Delta Force retaliates'': Delta Force storms the room with full force but accidentally forgets to bring Ameya back. Instead, they bring the Pragyaan trophies, which are now being held hostage as collateral. ''Ameya’s Revenge'' : Ameya hacks into the Pragyaan main site, replacing the homepage with a live stream of Jagan attempting to rap while wearing noise-canceling headphones. It’s as painful as it is entertaining. ''Revolt at Pragyaan:'' The entire Pragyaan organizing team stages a sit-in outside the Delta Force room, chanting slogans like “No Football, No Peace.” Chaos ensues as Revant's crush is accidentally added to the group chat, and everyone’s darkest secrets come spilling out. ''Bhoopesh’s Master Plan'': Bhoopesh takes control of the situation, announcing a 24-hour hackathon to solve the issue. The hackathon has only one rule: You must work in complete silence while listening to elevator music. Jagan is the judge.
